Cursor Prompt — SEO Article Generator Demo
Project Overview
Build a demo web app for a client (bitzenmineria.com — Bitcoin mining niche, Spanish language). The app is a proof-of-concept that demonstrates automated SEO article generation using AI. The client fills a form with article data (title, meta description, editorial notes), the app generates a full SEO-optimized article in Spanish via Claude API, and displays it as a live blog post with a card in a blog listing — all in real time, no database.
This is a DEMO, not a production app. Everything lives in React state. No database, no CMS integration. The goal is to visually demonstrate the end-to-end flow during a client meeting.

Tech Stack
·	Next.js 15 (App Router, TypeScript, Server Components by default)
·	Tailwind CSS v4
·	Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) via @anthropic-ai/sdk
·	Deployment target: Vercel

CRITICAL — Design System (Clone from Portfolio)
DO NOT use generic AI/SaaS aesthetics. No blue/purple gradients, no glassmorphism cards, no "AI glow" effects, no generic dark themes with neon accents.
This app MUST use dark mode by default (add class="dark" to <html>). The portfolio is dark-dominant. The demo must feel like part of the same brand.
Clone the design language from the portfolio. Here are the exact tokens:
Color System (Dark Mode — primary mode)
·	Background:oklch(0.145 0 0) — near-black (#1a1a1a equivalent)
·	Foreground/Text:oklch(0.985 0 0) — near-white
·	Card background:oklch(0.205 0 0) — slightly lighter than bg (#2e2e2e equivalent)
·	Card foreground:oklch(0.985 0 0)
·	Primary accent:#ff4d00 — vibrant orange-red. Use this for CTAs, active states, key highlights. Do NOT overuse — reserve for primary actions and key visual anchors.
·	Primary foreground (on accent):#ffffff
·	Hero text:#f6f7fc — slightly blue-tinted white for hero/heading areas
·	Secondary surface:oklch(0.269 0 0) — used for secondary cards, badges, muted backgrounds
·	Secondary foreground:oklch(0.985 0 0)
·	Muted text:oklch(0.708 0 0) — for descriptions, timestamps, secondary info
·	Border:oklch(1 0 0 / 10%) — very subtle white at 10% opacity
·	Input border:oklch(1 0 0 / 15%) — slightly more visible for form fields
·	Ring/focus:oklch(0.556 0 0) — medium gray for focus rings
Fonts
·	Body font: Roboto (loaded via --font-roboto CSS variable, set as --font-sans)
·	Heading font: Anek Kannada (loaded via --font-anek-kannada, set as --font-heading)
·	Monospace:ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace
·	Load both Roboto and Anek Kannada from Google Fonts via next/font/google in the root layout. Apply headings font to all h1-h6 elements via CSS.
Border Radius
·	Base radius:0.625rem (10px)
·	Small (badges, tags):calc(0.625rem * 0.6) = ~6px
·	Medium (inputs, small cards):calc(0.625rem * 0.8) = ~8px
·	Large (cards, panels):0.625rem = 10px
·	XL (modals, large containers):calc(0.625rem * 1.4) = ~14px
Component Patterns
·	Cards: Use bg-card background with border border-border (the 10% white border). Padding p-6. Rounded rounded-lg. No box shadows.
·	Buttons (Primary):bg-[#ff4d00] text-white with hover:opacity-90 transition. Rounded rounded-md. Padding px-6 py-3. Font weight font-medium.
·	Buttons (Secondary/Ghost):bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground or bg-transparent border border-border text-foreground hover:bg-secondary.
·	Inputs:bg-transparent border border-input text-foreground rounded-md px-4 py-3. Focus state: focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring focus:border-transparent.
·	Badges/Tags:bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground rounded-sm px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium.
·	Transitions: All interactive elements get transition-all duration-150 ease-in-out. No bouncy animations, no spring physics.
Typography Hierarchy
·	Page titles (h1):font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-hero-text
·	Section headings (h2):font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-foreground
·	Subsection (h3):font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-foreground
·	Body text:font-sans text-base text-foreground leading-relaxed
·	Small/caption:font-sans text-sm text-muted-foreground
·	Monospace (code blocks, JSON):font-mono text-sm
General Design Rules
·	Dark mode is the ONLY mode. Do not implement light mode toggle.
·	Generous whitespace — minimum gap-6 between sections, py-16 for page sections.
·	Hierarchy through background shifts (bg → card → secondary), not shadows.
·	Borders are extremely subtle (10% white). Don't make them more visible.
·	The #ff4d00 orange is the ONLY color accent. Everything else is grayscale.
·	Hover states: opacity shift (hover:opacity-90) or subtle bg change (hover:bg-secondary). Never color shifts or scale transforms.
·	The app should feel like a natural extension of the portfolio — same DNA, same restraint.

