Environment Variables
Create .env.local:
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLIENT_DOMAIN=bitzenmineria.com

ALL config values must come from env vars or constants. Zero hardcoded API keys, URLs, or magic strings in components.

State Management
Use Zustand for client-side article storage. NO database. NO localStorage.
// /stores/useArticleStore.ts
interface ArticleStore {
  articles: GeneratedArticle[]
  currentArticle: GeneratedArticle | null
  isGenerating: boolean
  addArticle: (article: GeneratedArticle) => void
  setCurrentArticle: (article: GeneratedArticle | null) => void
  setIsGenerating: (val: boolean) => void
}

Articles persist in memory for the duration of the session. Refresh = gone. That's fine for a demo.

TypeScript Interfaces
// /lib/types.ts

export interface SeoMetadata {
  title: string              // 55-60 chars
  metaDescription: string    // 150-160 chars
  slug: string
  canonicalUrl: string
  keywords: string[]         // 8-12 keywords
  ogTitle: string
  ogDescription: string
  schemaMarkup: ArticleSchema
}

export interface ArticleSection {
  h2: string
  content: string            // HTML formatted paragraphs
  h3s?: {
    title: string
    content: string
  }[]
}

export interface FaqItem {
  question: string
  answer: string
}

export interface GeneratedArticle {
  seo: SeoMetadata
  article: {
    h1: string
    introduction: string
    sections: ArticleSection[]
    conclusion: string
    faq: FaqItem[]
  }
  internalLinkingSuggestions: string[]
  imageAltSuggestions: string[]
  createdAt: string          // ISO date string
}

export interface ArticleFormData {
  title: string
  metaDescription: string
  observations: string
}

export interface ArticleSchema {
  "@context": "https://schema.org"
  "@type": "Article"
  headline: string
  description: string
  author: {
    "@type": "Organization"
    name: string
  }
  datePublished: string
  keywords: string[]
}


API Route — /api/generate-article/route.ts
·	Accept POST with ArticleFormData body
·	Validate input (return 400 if missing required fields)
·	Build the prompt using the builder function from /lib/prompts.ts
·	Call Claude API with streaming enabled
·	Stream the response back to the client as a ReadableStream using TransformStream
·	Use claude-sonnet-4-20250514 model
·	Set max_tokens: 8000 (full articles need room)
·	The system prompt must instruct Claude to return ONLY valid JSON, no markdown fences, no preamble
Streaming approach:
·	Stream raw text chunks to the frontend for the live preview
·	The frontend accumulates chunks and once the stream is complete, parses the full JSON
·	If JSON parsing fails, show an error state with a retry button

System Prompt (in /lib/prompts.ts)
export const SYSTEM_PROMPT = `Eres un redactor SEO experto especializado en contenido sobre minería de criptomonedas y Bitcoin en español (España). 

Tu tarea: dado un título, meta descripción y notas editoriales, generas un artículo completo, listo para publicar, optimizado para posicionamiento en Google España.

REQUISITOS DEL ARTÍCULO:
- Longitud: 1800-2500 palabras
- Idioma: español de España (no latinoamericano)
- Tono: profesional pero accesible, dirigido a personas interesadas en minería de Bitcoin
- Usa la keyword principal de forma natural en: H1, primer párrafo, al menos 2 H2s, y la conclusión
- Densidad de keywords: 1-2% (natural, nunca forzado)
- Incluye datos actualizados de 2026 cuando sea relevante
- Párrafos cortos (3-4 líneas máximo) para facilitar lectura web
- Usa listas, negritas y formatos que mejoren la escaneabilidad

ESTRUCTURA OBLIGATORIA:
- Un H1 (puede ser el título optimizado o una variación)
- Introducción enganchante (2-3 párrafos)
- 4-6 secciones con H2 (y H3 donde sea necesario)
- Conclusión con CTA implícito
- Sección FAQ con 4-5 preguntas relevantes (optimizadas para featured snippets)

METADATOS SEO:
- Title tag: 55-60 caracteres
- Meta description: 150-160 caracteres
- 8-12 keywords relevantes (mix de short-tail y long-tail)
- Open Graph title y description
- JSON-LD schema markup (tipo Article)
- Sugerencias de enlaces internos basados en el dominio ${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_CLIENT_DOMAIN}
- Sugerencias de alt text para imágenes

El contenido HTML debe usar etiquetas semánticas: <p>, <strong>, <ul>, <li>, <h3>.
NO uses <h1> ni <h2> en el contenido — esos se renderizan por separado desde los campos estructurados.

RESPONDE ÚNICAMENTE con un objeto JSON válido. Sin backticks, sin markdown, sin texto antes o después del JSON. Solo el JSON puro.`

export function buildUserPrompt(data: ArticleFormData): string {
  return `DATOS DEL ARTÍCULO:

Título: ${data.title}
Meta descripción: ${data.metaDescription}
${data.observations ? `Observaciones editoriales: ${data.observations}` : ''}

Genera el artículo completo con todos los metadatos SEO.`
}


Page Behaviors
/admin — Generation Form
·	Three fields: título (required), meta descripción (required), observaciones (optional textarea)
·	"Generar y Publicar" button
·	On submit: POST to /api/generate-article, show streaming preview in a side panel or below the form
·	While streaming: show the raw text appearing in real time in a preview panel styled as a document
·	On complete: parse JSON, add to Zustand store, show success state with two buttons: "Ver Artículo" (links to /preview/[slug]) and "Ver Blog" (links to /preview)
·	On error: show error message with retry button
/preview — Blog Listing
·	Grid of ArticleCard components (3 cols desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile)
·	Each card shows: title, excerpt (first 150 chars of intro, strip HTML), date, keyword badges (first 3)
·	Cards link to /preview/[slug]
·	If no articles yet, show empty state: "No hay artículos generados todavía" with CTA to /admin
·	Pull articles from Zustand store
/preview/[slug] — Article Page
·	Render the full article with proper heading hierarchy
·	Below the article: collapsible "Datos SEO" panel showing all metadata in a clean formatted view (meta tags as code blocks, keywords as badges, JSON-LD as formatted JSON)
·	Sidebar or top bar with: "Copiar HTML", "Copiar Meta Tags", "Copiar Schema JSON-LD" buttons
·	Use Next.js client-side rendering (since data comes from Zustand, not server)
·	FAQ section rendered as an accordion

Code Quality Rules
1.	No any types. Everything typed. Use the interfaces from /lib/types.ts.
2.	No hardcoded strings in components. Colors in Tailwind config/CSS vars. Text constants in /lib/constants.ts. Config in env vars.
3.	Components are single-responsibility. A card component renders a card. It doesn't fetch data or manage state.
4.	Server vs Client boundary is explicit. Only mark components 'use client' when they need interactivity. Layout, headers, footers can be server components if they don't depend on Zustand.
5.	Error handling everywhere. API route validates input. Frontend handles loading, error, and empty states. Stream parsing has try/catch with fallback.
6.	No console.log in committed code. Use proper error states in UI.
7.	Responsive by default. Every component works on mobile. Use Tailwind responsive prefixes.
8.	Semantic HTML.<article>, <section>, <nav>, <header>, <main>, <footer>. This is an SEO demo — the HTML structure itself is part of the pitch.
9.	Import aliases. Use @/ path alias for all imports. No relative paths deeper than one level.
10.	Consistent file naming. PascalCase for components, camelCase for utils/hooks/stores, kebab-case for routes.

Implementation Order
1.	Set up Next.js 16 project with TypeScript, Tailwind, path aliases
2.	Set up design tokens (CSS variables in globals.css, matching portfolio)
3.	Build UI primitives (/components/ui/*) — Button, Input, Textarea, Card, Badge
4.	Build layout (Header, Footer, root layout)
5.	Build types and constants
6.	Build the Zustand store
7.	Build the API route with Claude integration (test with hardcoded form data first)
8.	Build the admin form and streaming preview
9.	Build the blog listing page and ArticleCard
10.	Build the article preview page with SEO metadata panel
11.	Polish: loading states, error states, empty states, transitions
12.	Test full flow end to end
13.	Deploy to Vercel

Dependencies to Install
npm install zustand @anthropic-ai/sdk

That's it. Keep it minimal. No UI libraries, no extra packages. Tailwind + Zustand + Anthropic SDK.
